relevance_explanation: The trimmed routine retains the error handling logic which should have been removed since this is a fallback that is not always used. Instead, the success or default case is primarily more relevant.
completeness_explanation: The first step of the original routine was checking the withdrawal eligibility, which was deemed eligible. This step was removed but should have been included within the routine, since eligibility can change at any time. The message indicating that the customer is eligible for withdrawal should be provided back to the customer.
